
# BANKSY Domain Analysis

Identifies recurring spatial tissue domains across all injury conditions and
timepoints by running BANKSY + Harmony per group, extracting domain expression
profiles, and clustering domains cross-condition into **meta-domains**.

## Overview

```
Merged .h5ad (all sections)
       │
       ▼
k_geom QC — median k-NN distances per group
       │
       ▼  (run once per GROUP_VALUE)
┌─────────────────────────────────────────┐
│  Per-group pipeline                     │
│  · Subset to one inj_type × timepoint  │
│  · Exclude low-quality batches          │
│  · Normalize (CPM) + log1p             │
│  · Stagger slide coords by batch        │
│  · BANKSY (λ=0.8) → PCA (25 PCs)      │
│  · Harmony batch correction             │
│  · Leiden clustering (two methods,      │
│    multiple resolutions)                │
│  · Save domain expression profiles      │
│  → adata_group_banksy_harmony.h5ad      │
│  → domain_profiles__*.csv              │
└─────────────────────────────────────────┘
       │  (repeat for all groups)
       ▼
┌─────────────────────────────────────────┐
│  Meta-domain discovery                  │
│  · Load all domain profiles             │
│  · Z-score genes across domains         │
│  · Pairwise domain-domain correlation   │
│  · Hierarchical clustering              │
│  · Cut dendrogram into t meta-domains   │
│  → meta_domains_mapping.csv            │
└─────────────────────────────────────────┘
```

## Why this approach?

Running BANKSY on the full merged dataset at once is computationally expensive
and conflates batch effects with biological variation. Instead, BANKSY is run
**per group** (one injury type × timepoint at a time), with Harmony correcting
for slide-to-slide batch effects within each group. The resulting domain
expression profiles (mean expression per Leiden cluster) are then compared
**across all groups** via pairwise Pearson correlation to find domains that
are transcriptionally similar regardless of when or where they appear.
Hierarchical clustering of this correlation matrix defines the final
**meta-domains** — tissue compartments that are reproducible across conditions.

## Two clustering methods

Each group is clustered two ways after Harmony correction, providing
complementary views at the same resolutions:

| Method | Implementation | Notes |
|---|---|---|
| **BANKSY-style Leiden** | `run_Leiden_partition` on BANKSY PCs | Spatially-aware — uses the full BANKSY graph structure |
| **Scanpy-style Leiden** | `sc.pp.neighbors` + `sc.tl.leiden` on `X_pca_harmony` | Standard graph-based clustering, faster |

Both are saved as separate columns in `adata.obs` and exported as domain
profile CSVs. In practice the meta-domain step is run on one method's
profiles (default: BANKSY-style at resolution 0.5).

## Usage

**Step 1 — QC:** run the k-NN distance cell to determine the best `k_geom`
for each group. A higher median distance → consider increasing `k_geom`.

**Step 2 — Per-group pipeline:** for each group, set:
```python
GROUP_VALUE = "inj_1_d5"   # must match a value in adata.obs["inj_type_per_day"]
k_geom = 8                  # spatial neighbourhood size from QC
```
then run the pipeline cell. Repeat for all groups.

**Step 3 — Meta-domains:** once all groups are processed, run the
meta-domain cell. Adjust `t` to control the number of meta-domains:
```python
t = 9   # number of meta-domains to cut from the dendrogram
```

## Key parameters

| Parameter | Default | Description |
|---|---|---|
| `k_geom` | 8 | BANKSY spatial neighbourhood size — set per-group from QC |
| `lambda_list` | `[0.8]` | BANKSY mixing weight (0 = no neighbourhood) |
| `pca_dim` | 25 | PCA components before Harmony |
| `max_iter_harmony` | 50 | Harmony iterations |
| `resolutions` | `[0.3, 0.5, 0.8, 1.0, 1.2]` | Leiden clustering resolutions (both methods) |
| `scanpy_n_neighbors` | 30 | Neighbours for scanpy graph |
| `spacing_factor` | 2.0 | Spacing between staggered slides in visualisation |
| `t` | 9 | Number of meta-domains |

## Input

A merged `.h5ad` with:

| Field | Description |
|---|---|
| `adata.X` | Raw count matrix (integers) |
| `adata.obs["inj_type_per_day"]` | Group label (e.g. `inj_1_d5`) |
| `adata.obs["batch"]` | Slide/section ID |
| `adata.obs["x"]`, `adata.obs["y"]` | Spatial coordinates |

## Outputs

**Per group** (saved to `OUT_DIR/<GROUP_VALUE>/`):

| File | Description |
|---|---|
| `adata_group_banksy_harmony.h5ad` | Integrated object with `counts` + `lognorm` layers, BANKSY/Harmony embeddings, and all cluster columns |
| `domain_profiles__BANKSY__<key>.csv` | Mean log-normalized expression per BANKSY domain |
| `domain_profiles__SCANPY__<key>.csv` | Mean log-normalized expression per Scanpy domain |
| `domain_sizes__*.csv` | Cell count per domain |
| `UMAP_domains_grid__<group>.png` | UMAP grid across all resolutions and methods |
| `SPATIAL__HARMONY__<group>.png` | Spatial projection of Harmony/Scanpy clusters |
| `SPATIAL__BANKSY__<group>.png` | Spatial projection of BANKSY clusters |
| `stagger_check.png` | QC plot of staggered slide layout |

**Meta-domain step:**

| File | Description |
|---|---|
| `meta_domains_mapping.csv` | Maps each `<group>__<domain>` to a meta-domain ID |

## Output layers & embeddings

| Key | Location | Description |
|---|---|---|
| `counts` | `adata.layers` | Raw integer counts |
| `lognorm` | `adata.layers` | CPM-normalized + log1p |
| `X_pca_harmony` | `adata.obsm` | Harmony-corrected PCA (25 PCs) |
| `X_umap_harmony` | `adata.obsm` | UMAP of Harmony embedding |
| `harmony_leiden_<r>` | `adata.obs` | Scanpy Leiden labels per resolution |
| `banksy_<params>` | `adata.obs` | BANKSY Leiden labels per resolution |

## Requirements

```
scanpy · banksy · harmonypy · scipy · numpy · pandas · matplotlib · seaborn · joblib
```
